Repository licensing (scope)

This repository is a multi-license monorepo. The MIT License above governs the
repository-level tooling and configuration and every first-party game that
declares MIT. It is NOT a blanket license over the whole tree.

Each package under `packages/` ships its OWN `LICENSE` file, and that per-package
file is authoritative for that package. When a package's license differs from
the MIT above, the package's own `LICENSE` controls.

| Package                  | License      | Note                                              |
|--------------------------|--------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| packages/dino-runner     | MIT          | bundled assets: see its THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md    |
| packages/fruit-slash     | MIT          | no third-party code or assets                     |
| packages/leaf-memory     | MIT          | no third-party code or assets                     |
| packages/whack-a-monkey  | MIT          | bundled assets: see its THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md    |
| packages/phobos          | GPL-2.0-only | links the GPL DOOM engine; see packages/phobos/LICENSE + THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md |

GPL-2.0-only applies to the `packages/phobos` package only. Under the GNU GPL
version 2 section 2 (mere aggregation), distributing phobos alongside the MIT
games in this repository does not place those other games under the GPL: each
game is a separate work that does not link or derive from the DOOM engine.

For bundled third-party code and assets within a package (for example the
BSD-3-Clause Chromium sprites in dino-runner, the CC0 Kenney art in
whack-a-monkey, or the BSD-3-Clause Freedoom data in phobos), see that package's
`THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md`.
